  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The hotel serves a varied continental buffet breakfast with locally sourced ingredients, including fresh pastries, breads, cereals, juices, tea and coffee. If you upgrade to half board you'll get a choice of four courses for dinner.</p>
<p>The hotel’s restaurant is located in the romantic courtyard and offers sensational dishes to be enjoyed al fresco – a retractable roof is used for when the weather is less pleasant. Seasonal local specialities include Bistecca alla Fiorentina as well as other Tuscan and Mediterranean dishes, all of which are accompanied by fine wines. Taste the Aetos Wine, produced by the hotel owners and try the hotels home made olive oil and home grown herbs. </p>
<p>The Piano Bar is an ideal spot for a pre or post dinner drink, with a cosy atmosphere and music. For cocktails, head to the panoramic terrace -  we can recommend the hotel's own "Negroni Barrique Adler" cocktail</p>]]></cateringDescription>
